{{Infobox film | name = Dialogues with Madwomen | image = | image size = | border = | alt = | caption = | director = Allie Light | producer = Irving Saraf | writer = | screenplay = | story = | narrator = | starring = | music = | cinematography = Irving Saraf | editing = Irving Saraf | studio = | distributor = | released = <!-- {{Film date|Year|Month|Day|Location}} --> | runtime = 90 minutes | country = United States | language = English | budget = | gross = }} '''''Dialogues with Madwomen''''' is a 1993 [[Documentary film|documentary]] by [[Allie Light]] focusing on [[mental illness]] in women.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wmm.com/filmcatalog/pages/c141.shtml | title=Dialogues with Madwomen | publisher=''[[Women Make Movies]]'' | accessdate=1 December 2014}}</ref>
==Synopsis== In ''Dialogues with Madwomen'', filmmakers Allie Light and Irving Saraf have seven "madwomen" — including Light herself — into telling their stories. Using a mixture of home movies, archival footage of [[psychiatric]] wards, re-enactments, and interviews with their subjects, Light and Saraf have created a complex, moving portrait of women in whom [[Depression (mood)|depression]], [[schizophrenia]], and [[multiple personalities]] coexist with powerful, sometimes inspired levels of creativity.
==See also== *[[Atypical antipsychotic]]s, which came onto the market after this film was made
==Karen Wong== In December 2013, a man whose DNA linked him to Karen Wong, one of the seven women in the film, was found guilty and convicted for her murder.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfexaminer.com/sanfrancisco/man-convicted-in-1991-rape-murder-of-richmond-district-woman/Content?oid=2658190 | title=Man convicted in 1991 rape, murder of Richmond district woman | date=24 December 2013 | accessdate=1 December 2014 |publisher=''[[The San Francisco Examiner]]''}}</ref> His conviction was later overturned. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sfgate.com/bayarea/article/S-F-murder-conviction-overturned-judge-6785615.php | title=S.F. murder conviction overturned - judge tossed holdout juror | date=26 January 2016 | accessdate=14 April 2017 |publisher=''[[SFGATE]]''}}</ref>
