{{Infobox book | name = The James Deans | image = The James Deans.jpg | author = [[Reed Farrel Coleman]] | genre = [[Mystery fiction]], [[Thriller genre|Thriller]], [[Crime novel|Crime]] | published = 2005 | publisher = [[Plume (publisher)|Plume]] | isbn = 978-0-452-28650-4 | alt = The James Deans | pages = 288 | website = {{URL|http://reedcoleman.com/books/the-james-deans/|The James Deans}} | awards = [[Anthony Award|Anthony Award for Best Paperback Original]] (2006) }}
'''The James Deans''' is a book written by [[Reed Farrel Coleman]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.simonandschuster.co.uk/books/The-James-Deans/Reed-Farrel-Coleman/9781440541018|title=The James Deans eBook by Reed Farrel Coleman {{!}} Official Publisher Page|last=|first=|date=|website=Simon & Schuster|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://reedcoleman.com/books/the-james-deans/|title=The James Deans|last=|first=|date=|website=Reed Farrel Coleman|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> and published by [[Plume (publisher)|Plume]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-452-28650-4|title=Fiction Book Review: THE JAMES DEANS: A Moe Prager Mystery by Reed Farrel Coleman|work=PublishersWeekly.com|access-date=2017-03-22|language=en}}</ref> on 25 January 2005, which later went on to win the [[Anthony Award]] for Best Paperback Original in 2006.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/2000s/|title=Winners and Nominees 2000s|date=2015-09-22|work=Bouchercon|access-date=2017-03-22|language=en}}</ref>
